25|$|Justice Samuel Alito {{delivered}} {{the opinion of}} the Court, joined by Chief Justice John Roberts and Justices Antonin Scalia, Anthony Kennedy <b>and</b> <b>Clarence</b> <b>Thomas.</b> According to the Court, the Eighth Amendment requires prisoners to show there is a known and available alternative method of execution. The prisoners had failed to do this, the Court found, because the alternative drugs they proposed were unavailable to Oklahoma. The Court explained that Hill v. McDonough (2006) did not apply.|$|E
