50|$|In a {{unanimous}} decision handed down on February 23, 2011, the Court unanimously (8-0, with Justice Elena Kagan not {{taking part in}} this case) reversed the California courts and held that federal preemption does not apply. Justice Stephen Breyer wrote {{the decision of the}} court. Justice Sonia Sotomayor wrote a concurring opinion, <b>and</b> Justice <b>Clarence</b> <b>Thomas</b> wrote an opinion concurring in the judgment.|$|R
